Caravel Openframe for IHP SG13CMOS5L
---------------------------------------------------------

These instructions are currently very incomplete.

The top level layout is "caravel_openframe.mag"

To create a new openframe chip with a custom user project:

(1)  Clone or fork this repository.  You probably want to create
     a new branch for the project;  then each project has the
     same upstream openframe repository but exists in its own
     development branch.
(2)  Run the script scripts/setup.sh to import IHP open PDK
     library views into local .mag files
(3)  Add verilog for the user project in ../verilog/rtl/
(4)  The user project verilog top level should be named
     "openframe_user_project" in file "openframe_user_project.v",
     replacing the template file.
(5)  If there are multiple verilog files in the user project,
     either include them from the top level verilog or add them
     to "netlists.v"
(6)  Most scripts are run from the mag/ directory.
(7)  Set the user ID for the project with ../scripts/set_user_id.sh.
(8)  Do a top-level extraction for LVS with ../scripts/run_extract.sh
(9)  Run LVS with run_lvs.sh in the ../lvs/ directory.
(10) Generate final GDS using the script ../scripts/run_gen_gds.sh


Generating the user project example
-------------------------------------------------------------------
The user project example in this repository is a framework for
an analog "sub-harness" capable of aggregating a number of analog
projects, each one able to be separately powered.

The user project has dependent libraries which are hierarchical
and therefore also independent git projects.  They should be
instantiated as git submodules.  The submodules can be cloned with
the project by doing

git clone https://github.com/RTimothyEdwards/sg13cmos5l_ocd_ip__openframe.git --recurse-submodules

or after cloning, by doing

git submodule update --init --recursive

That initializes the dependent repositories used for the project
example.  For a different project, new submodules can be added by
first creating the IP as a git project, use

git submodule add <repository_URL>

For simplicity, keep the subdirectory name the same as the repository.
After adding the submodule, commit and push as usual.
